# Lets you rename commands without editing code -- useful once you have
# enough commands that some names collide with other bots, or just feel
# too generic (e.g. !skip is an extremely common bot command name).
#
# Format, one per line:
#   original_command=new_name
#
# Once an alias is set, the ORIGINAL name stops working entirely. !sr
# will not do anything once "sr=songreq" is active below -- only
# !songreq will. This is intentional, so there's never a confusing
# situation with two different working names for the same thing.
#
# Changes here only take effect after restarting the bot -- aliases are
# read once at startup, not watched live.
#
# Copy this file to command_aliases.txt (without .example) and edit it,
# then restart the bot. Lines starting with # are comments and ignored.
# Leave a command out entirely to keep its original name.
#
# Available commands: sr, remove, vol, skip, sq, song
# (setperm and perms are intentionally not aliasable -- they're
# mod/admin tools, not viewer-facing commands)

# sr=songreq
# skip=voteskip
# vol=volume
